description:
&lt;p&gt;Free Spirits is a busy 88 place Nursery, graded Outstanding by Ofsted. The Nursery caters for children 6 months to Pre School, located within the grounds of The Freeman Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you ready to join an Outstanding Nursery setting?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy has arisen within the Nursery for a full time member of staff to join our ‘Outstanding’ team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a passionate and energetic member of staff with a sound knowledge of the Early Years Foundation Stage and child development. Could you be this person?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you enthusiastic about working with children and supporting their learning and development?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you able to use your own initiative, research and keep your knowledge up to date?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of a team would you be able to plan varied and stimulating activities which challenge children’s learning and development?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome applications from candidates who would like an opportunity to join our ‘Outstanding’ team. A sound knowledge of The Early Years Foundation Stage and a positive approach to child care is essential. Experience working with babies would be desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A minimum of NVQ level 2 &lt;strong&gt;in childcare&lt;/strong&gt; or an equivalent &lt;strong&gt;in childcare&lt;/strong&gt; is essential. An NVQ level 3 &lt;strong&gt;in childcare&lt;/strong&gt; or an equivalent &lt;strong&gt;in childcare&lt;/strong&gt; would be desirable. &lt;strong&gt;Please ensure that your qualification is in childcare before you apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time 37 Hours 30 minutes/week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marika Knotts, Nicky Wagstaff or Emma Crowe on 0191 2231888&lt;/p&gt;
